# Snowstorm PoC conventions

## Proof of concept

Keep code **absolutely minimal** and **easy to read**. Prefer the smallest change that works. Avoid extra layers, premature generalization, and dependencies unless they clearly reduce complexity for this PoC.

## Runtime

Use **Node.js** for scripts, CLIs, and any runtime code in this repo.

## Environment variables

- Keep **`.env.sample`** in the project root with **placeholder** values only (no real credentials).
- When introducing or changing config, update **`.env.sample`** and **tell the user** to copy or merge into their real **`.env`** as needed.
- Never commit real secrets; use a local **`.env`** (ignored by git).
